      • isInCuboidRegion

        public boolean isInCuboidRegion(Vector3N min,
                                Vector3N max,
                                Vector3N vec)
        Returns true if vec is inside the 3D cuboid defined by the two furthest points min and max. Assuming this is your cuboid, min represents point D, max represents point F, and vec is represented by point I.
        Parameters:
        min - The minimum vector of the cuboid region
        max - The maximum vector of the cuboid region
        vec - The vector position in 3D space
        Returns:
        true if vec is inside the 3D cuboid region
        See Also:
        isInCuboidRegion(int, int, int, int, int, int, int, int, int)

      • isInCuboidRegion

        @Contract(pure=true)
public boolean isInCuboidRegion(int x_min,
                                                      int x_max,
                                                      int y_min,
                                                      int y_max,
                                                      int z_min,
                                                      int z_max,
                                                      int x,
                                                      int y,
                                                      int z)
        Returns true if a vector defined by x, y, z is inside the 3D cuboid defined by the two furthest points min and max. Each point is represented by 3 integer values, x, y, and z. Assuming this is your cuboid, min represents point D, max represents point F, and vec is represented by point I.
        Parameters:
        x_min - The position of the minimum vector on the X axis
        x_max - The position of the maximum vector on the X axis
        y_min - The position of the minimum vector on the Y axis
        y_max - The position of the maximum vector on the Y axis
        z_min - The position of the minimum vector on the Z axis
        z_max - The position of the maximum vector on the Z axis
        x - The position of the vector on the X axis
        y - The position of the vector on the Y axis
        z - The position of the vector on the Z axis
        Returns:
        true if the defined vector is inside the 3D cuboid region
